b'Wow, your narrative is horribly flawed. "Guided the Saints through Katrina?" He was openly fighting to have them permanently moved to San Antonio while the city was still reeling from the aftermath. This was after he\'d spent a few of the previous years sucking more and more $$$ from New Orleans and Louisiana, despite already having what many considered the best "sweetheart deal" in the 4 major sports leagues. He was even fighting then Commissioner Paul Tagliabue over having to play 3 "home games" at LSU that season. Tagliabiue was also the one who stepped in and prevented the Saints from leaving after the 2005 season. Also, Mr.Benson wasn\'t the one that "opened the Superdome to storm victims." That was Mayor Nagin and the city who declared it as "a shelter of last resort." Make no mistake, Mr. Benson purchasing the team in 1985 saved New Orleans from losing the Saints then and he went on to do many great things for the city and for Saints fans. That said, he had more than his share of flaws.'

b"I'm not a Darnold fan myself. I do think he's overrated and just cashing in on his high stock. b'As a Broncos' fan all I can say is THANK GOD. Also, please go ahead and take Allen. Here is a 5 game sample from Allen just last year...
TM      CMP ATT YDS TD INT
Iowa      23   40   174  0    2
Oregon  9     24    64   0    1
Hawaii   9     29    92   1    0
BSU       12    27  131  1    2
CSU       10    20  138  0    0

Totals    63   130 599  2   5

The NFL QB position is all about accuracy, FB IQ, leadership, quick decisions and receiver spatial awareness in relation to the defense. Allen struggled mightily with locking on guys post snap and usually missed a bunch of "gimme" throws that have to be made at the next level. If the Super Bowl is still on your DVR go look at all of the completions that both Foles and Brady made that day. None of those game-changing, drop-in-the-bucket, throw-before-they're-open throws would've hit their target with Allen. No rocket arm was needed. Just look at Peyton Manning's record setting season with Denver in 2013. He couldn't throw it over 45 yards to save his life. It didn't matter though. It's all about accuracy, timing & awareness. This is why the NFL GM's continue to miss on QBs. They value size/athleticism over skill/production. The two most accurate and productive college QBs of the last 10 years were Kellen Moore and Case Keenum. Neither got drafted. Not because of their production but because their size and perceived lack of arm strength. Only Keenum got a legitimate shot and that was only because of a string of injuries to guys ahead of him in Minnesota. Just look at this highlight video of Kellen Moore. Notice the back to back 60 yard throws at 3:40 into the video. More than enough arm for the NFL. Guys like Keenum and Moore are the next Drew Brees or Peyton Manning. Too bad Moore is now a coach with Dallas. He should be given a shot somewhere. Not the big, athletic guys with rocket arms and little else. https://youtu.be/RYESEnLNIPE [[VIDEO_SHARE_YOUTUBE]]'
